[34:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to edit out. Now, initially when we use this text to image workflow and we loaded this latent image node, this basically generates a frame of random noise. So, we want to edit out 100% of that random noise and turn it into our'

[35:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'prompt. But here, since we\'re uploading a reference image as the input, we don\'t want to, you know, completely remove 100% of this. We want some of this image to influence our final generation. So, basically, this den noiseise value is'

[35:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'like how much influence you want this original image to have. A lower value would have higher influence. A higher value would give it more room to change this image a lot more. So for us, let\'s try something like 0.5. And then let me'

[35:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
